title: Police: YouTube teen died after medical emergency
text:
Police: YouTube teen known for family life, game videos died after medical emergency at home By BRIAN WITTE Associated Press   05, 2015 - 4:01 pmLast Updated: October 05, 2015 - 4:01 pm   
Subjects: 
Maryland (376) 

ANNAPOLIS, Maryland — Police say a 13-year-old Maryland boy known for appearing in his family's video blog and his own YouTube posts about playing the game Minecraft died after a medical emergency. 
Anne Arundel County Police said Monday that Caleb LeBlanc died Thursday at a hospital. Police and members of the fire department responded to his home about 7 p.m. and found him suffering an "unknown medical emergency." Police say in a release that "there are no suspicious circumstances" and that there is no criminal investigation. 
Police say a medical examiner will determine a cause of death. 
Lt. Ryan Frashure says Caleb is known as Caleb Logan Bratayley in his family's online video series called "Bratayleys."
